    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_jiaocaineedrop_chem-97961.pdf_128_3",
    "text": "As with salt, sugar has radically different properties (both physical and chemical) than its constituent elements. This difference in properties, of constituent elements and compounds, is a central feature of chemical reactions.",
